            <title>[SOLR-2008] SolrCore.close should shutdown updateHandler before searchExecutor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2008</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As noted on the mailing list...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://markmail.org/message/cvihm2m6aqhrfbo5&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://markmail.org/message/cvihm2m6aqhrfbo5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a RejectedExecutionException can occur when shutting down a solr core if the UpdateHandler.close() wants to do an autocommit - because the searchExecutor has already been closed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
